You know I didn't want to give it a full 5 stars just cuz I don't want the hoard of foodies coming down and causing a long wait for food. This place is small, so don't come here expecting a seat readily available. For single or couple's this place is fine to dine in. But I would recommend takeout. The tortillas are made fresh and honestly that makes a huge difference in the taco eating experience. Portions are big, you'll have to learn to ask the ladies  in there to describe how big some of the tacos or sopes are before you order for one and get a taco that's family size.
